o  Weapons that kill a single type of monster each time they are used.
   Make only one for each monster type.  Make some of them ranged weapons.
   A noble can only carry one such weapon at once (your "trade up" idea).
 
o  Red slippers that return the noble -- and just the noble -- to the
   location where he or she was formed ("There's no place like home...").
   Any troops or other items carried by the noble will be given to the
   noble's stack leader or the first noble stacked under the noble or
   they will be dropped if there is no one to give the items to.  
 
o  Items that allow all the available resources of one kind in a location 
   (e.g. wood, stone, etc.) to be taken in one day by one noble (e.g.
   a magic axe, a magic pick, a magic shovel, a magic rope, etc.).  Do a
   sanity check on this one first but it shouldn't be too harmful for
   the basic resources since most determined factions can all but do
   this, anyway, with workers.
 
o  Some sort of device that allows a certain weight to walk across water
   without a boat.  Perhaps a magic raft.
 
o  A magical hound that works like the real ones -- perhaps a little
   bit better.



