Take auraculum notification.  No doubt the players who auraculated
later in the game complained that notification put them at an unfair
advantage.  Strictly speaking, that's of course true.  But doesn't
that add some spice and interest to the game, knowing that if you do
this thing you'll be challenging a power structure?  Doesn't it make
it interesting to rush to be the first to auraculate?  It makes the
decision on when to auraculate interesting as well.  Wait, and be more
powerful?  Or auraculate sooner and get the drop on others who follow?

